I recently got a Macan loaner from the dealership and got to drive it for 2.5 weeks. There are a few design flaws I found.
1. Seatbelt warning would not go away even when i buckled it up. It wasn't every time but I noticed it at least 7-10 times for the 2.5 weeks. I would say that's a lot. Maybe it is only to this specific vehicle. 
2. The footwell right to the accelerator is too close to the pedal. when I shift my right foot from brake to gas pedal, the front of my shoe always gets snagged by the foot well. On the same note, when I try to hit brake from gas pedal, my shoe also gets caught by the wall and I almost lost the timing to brake a couple of times. Very poor design. It may not be an issue if you use both feet to gas and brake but most don't. (I wrote this b4 watching his video but just finished watching his and he said something about it too. It's just that I didn't understand him cuz he mumbles under his breath when he talks about it. I get annoyed when he does that. It's hard for me to understand some of his brit accents :(). 
3. The brake has almost no play. Way too sensitive. Either you brake hard or you don't. I wonder if Cayenne of 2020 is also like that. My 911 and 2017 Cayenne aren't like that. 
Otherwise, you can expect same excellent drivability and handling from Porsche. I wasn't a big fan of gear ratio either but I didn't haul anything at that time so it may be ok with loading.
